<h1 class="title">Cosmic Muons</h1>
<p>
Cosmic rays from outer space turn into muons in the upper atmosphere.
</p>

<p>
Pass through 12''<sup>3</sup> block of fancy plastic 
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>Emit brief (~ns) flash of light</li>
<li>Viewed on both sides by photo-multipliers</li>
</ul>

<p>
Some Actually stop
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>µ→eνν the es also emit a flash of light</li>
</ul>

<p>
If we can measure the Δt between flashes can measure how long the stopped muons last. 
</p>

<p>
&lt;u&gt;Equipment&lt;/u&gt; 
</p>
<ul class="org-ul">
<li>PMT need high voltage 2k V</li>
<li>"fast electronics" to process &amp; digitize signals</li>
<li>TDC -&gt; digital time -&gt; histogram on computer</li>
</ul>
<p>
(Oscilloscope as debugger)
</p>

<p>
Lifetime of the muon is a big deal. Its how we measure the strength of the weak force!
Existence of µs at sea level proof relativity is correct. 
</p>

